problems.solution:
Submit a command group; **single_task** runs one work item.

```
#include <sycl/sycl.hpp>
#include <cstdio>

int main() {
    sycl::queue q(sycl::default_selector_v);
    q.submit([&](sycl::handler& h) {
        h.single_task([=]() { /* one work item */ });
    });
    q.wait();
    printf("Single task submitted\n");
    return 0;
}
```

**Explanation:** **q.submit()** takes a lambda with **sycl::handler&**. **h.single_task()** enqueues one work item. **q.wait()** blocks until done.

Output: Single task submitted

